summary: An ordinance relating to the general municipal election to be held March 12, 1935; providing for the submission of the proposed Charter Amendments contemplated by Resolution No. 11514 and No. 11515; requiring the City Comptroller and ex-officio City Clerk to certify to the Election Board of King County, Washington, as required by law, said proposed amendments in the form of specified ballot titles and said amendmetns in full; and declaring an emergency.
